cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

The paper proposes a new visual tracking algorithm that uses a hybrid of convolutional neural networks and traditional hand-crafted features, which is a common approach in computer vision (cs.CV). The algorithm also includes an online classifier and a re-detection module, which involves machine learning techniques such as incremental SVM and Gaussian mixture probability hypothesis density filter, indicating relevance to machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper deals with video sequences, which suggests multimedia (cs.MM) as another possible category. Finally, the problem of tracking a target in both sparse and crowded environments involves robotics (cs.RO) as a potential sub-category.
